headline: CrowdStrike and ExtraHop® Expand Partnership to Stop Shadow AI Risks
summary: AUSTIN, Texas & SAN FRANCISCO, April 30, 2025--RSAC 2025 – CrowdStrike (NASDAQ: CRWD) and ExtraHop today announced an expanded partnership to help enterprises detect and contain shadow AI risks. By ingesting market-leading network intelligence from ExtraHop into CrowdStrike Falcon® Next-Gen SIEM, the new integration gives SOC teams real-time visibility into unauthorized AI service usage and the ability to automate response actions – protecting sensitive data without slowing innovation.

headline: Nasdaq Bear Market: 2 Magnificent Stocks Down 6% and 14% You'll Regret Not Buying on the Dip
summary: The Nasdaq Composite index slipped into bear market territory in April, after President Trump imposed tariffs on America's trading partners.  Digital products and services are largely exempt from tariffs, so cybersecurity vendors like CrowdStrike and Palo Alto Networks are mostly unaffected.  Following President Donald Trump's "Liberation Day" tariff announcement on April 2, the Nasdaq Composite technology index plunged by as much as 24% from its record high, placing it in a technical bear market.
